# ML Feature System

`lib/ml/features.js` is the **single source of truth** for feature definitions. NEVER duplicate feature extraction logic.

## Adding a New Feature

1. Add to `FEATURE_DEFINITIONS` array in `lib/ml/features.js`
2. Add extraction logic in `extractFeatures()` in the same file
3. Update `FEATURE_NAMES` in `lib/config.js` to match
4. Run `npm run check:features` to verify alignment
5. Run `npm run train` to retrain the model
6. The server auto-reloads via file watcher — no restart needed

## Rules

- `src/train-model.js` calls `extractCityFeatures()` from `lib/ml/features.js` for per-city vectors
- `src/server.js` calls the same `extractFeatures()` for inference
- NEVER create a parallel feature extraction function
- Feature order MUST match `FEATURE_DEFINITIONS` exactly
- `lib/ml/validate-model.js` catches mismatches at server startup

## Current Features (17)

Geographic (7): dist_to_center, bearing_sin, bearing_cos, city_lat, city_lng, center_lat, center_lng
Context (2): countdown, warning_delay_minutes
Historical (2): city_historical_red_rate, city_avg_orange_to_red_minutes
Temporal (2): hour_sin, hour_cos
Multi-missile (4): multi_missile_detected, cluster_separation_km, gap_orange_percentage, city_in_minority_cluster

## Removed Features (do NOT re-add)

- `orange_zone_size` — not predictive, caused extrapolation on large waves
- `green_zone_count`, `dist_to_nearest_green`, `green_within_15km` — data leakage (green marks post-impact)
